                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d305">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1115/12–248: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cabot</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="11" xml:id="d305fn11">Repeated to the Ambassador in China
                        as telegram No. 1771.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-12-04T11:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 4, 1948—11 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2104. Dept opinion not desirable provide American guard (urtel 2611 Dec 2 rptd
                    Nanking 1972) as part international force for UN Hqrs, Shanghai. Appropriate
                    assistance to UN foreign representatives should be provided under US Govt
                    emergency plans to assist evacuation foreign nationals.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lovett</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
